@NODE "Prefs"

  akGIFPrefs
  -----------
  akGIFPrefs is the Preferences Program for akGIF.datatype.

  GUI has been designed with StormWizard 2.0, so this program needs
  "wizard.library" V42+ (you can find a copy on Aminet under
  "biz/haage/WizardLibrary.lha" or even never versions under
  ftp.haage-partner.com).

  Icon by Bert Bosma <lmb@wxs.nl> (based on NewIcons).

  Task (process) specific settings also can be done - either using
  the preferences program (which allows to select the corresponding
  process from a list as long as it actually is running at the same
  time) or by hand, following the scheme below:

                           OPTIONAL
  ---------------- task specific settings files -----------------------
  Settings specific to different caller programs may be created
  by copying the global settings from "Datatypes/akGIF.prefs" to an
  optional task-related prefs file called

            "Datatypes/akGIF.prefs_Tasks/TaSkNaMe"

  where "TaSkNaMe" means the name of the program as e.g. shown by
  a system monitor (for obvious reasons, this does work best with
  workbench programs, which don't require name patterns as some
  CLI programs might do, like for example "CLI(3):Work:Browsers/XWebber").
  So, with AWeb for example, you would just edit your global settings
  file and then do the following:

    MakeDir ENV:Datatypes/akGIF.prefs_Tasks
    Copy ENV:Datatypes/akGIF.prefs ENV:Datatypes/akGIF.prefs_Tasks/AWebIP"

     [... and the same for ENVARC: ...]

  After that, AWeb will ignore the global settings and fetch its own
  from the given file.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  Public options (available via prefs program):

   STRIPALPHA=<ON|OFF>          => see prefs program
   TILED_LOADING=<ON|OFF>       => see prefs program
   ANIM_LOADING=
        <FIRST|LAST|ALL>        => see prefs program
   SWAPALPHA=<ON|OFF>           => see prefs program
   TRANSTOALPHA=<ON|OFF>        => see prefs program (*)

  (*) For non-tile images this means that the single-color
      transparency directly is converted to ARGB/RGBA. Otherwise
      however it still would be available as plain single color
      transparency. For 24 bit GIF (multi-palette) tiles
      single/multi color transparency this option also does
      not matter since it becomes 32 bit ARGB/RGBA unless STRIPALPHA
      is set. However for 8 bit GIF multi color transparency only
      becomes 32 bit ARGB/RGBA in case TRANSTOALPHA is also set
      (otherwise it is ignored, since it is not clear which one of the
      different transparent colors should be made transparent in
      the 8 bit enforced single transparent color case).

  Hidden options (not available via prefs program):

   CUSTOM_MODES=<0x...hexID...> => use a fixed viewmode always
   NOASPECT                     => use fixed 1:1 aspect always
                                   (no calculation, faster)
   DEBUG                        => enable debug mode (output)

  WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS version does not support
           alpha channel handling, then always set STRIPALPHA=ON
           (no ARGB/RGBA)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

 History
 =======
 V45.95 (30.12.2008): - removed MOS support, as there are more
                        frequent MOS updates now and as there still
                        is no fully featured new SDK for external 
                        developers; makes semi-redundant datatype
                        development finally quite pointless
                      - copyright bump

 V45.90 (13.9.2008):  - updated TestDTAlpha tool and check for
                        PICDTALPHA
                      - added STRIPALPHA description to .guide

 V45.87 (16.1.2008):  - fixed version/date strings for V45.86
                      - for tiled images now also other types
                        of transparency/alpha are supported:

                         - 24 bit GIF (multi-palette) tiles
                           single/multi color transparency becomes
                           32 bit ARGB/RGBA
                         - 8 bit GIF multi color transparency
                           becomes 32 bit ARGB/RGBA in case
                           TRANSTOALPHA is set (otherwise ignored,
                           since it is not clear which of the
                           different transparent colors should
                           be made transparent in the single
                           color 8 bit case)

                      - added STRIPALPHA option
                      - fixed minor mem-leak related to extra
                        buffers for alpha and alpha-mapped
                        transparency
                      - fixed newly introduced race condition
                      - avoid multiple level 2 buffering setup
                      - fixed the viewmode fix from V45.86
                        a second time
                      - MOS: switched compiler (same as SV5)
                             and enabled optimizer

 V45.86 (6.1.2008):   - fixed bug in TRANSTOALPHA (oops)
                      - fixed long-standing MOS bug in viewmode
                        generation routine (did not occur with 68k
                        and did only pop up with some graphics)

 V45.85 (4.1.2008):   - MOS/68k: now really building from same
                                 source tree; the following
                                 information is relative to
                                 the former MOS tree
                      - improved MOS startup code
                      - added TRANSTOALPHA and SWAPALPHA options
                      - documented all prefs settings again
                        in the @{"Prefs" LINK Prefs} section
                      - Prefs: made the labels easier to understand,
                               especially the 24 bit / tile settings

 V45.84 (2.1.2008):   - some additions to asyncio routines
                      - improvements in asyncio routines

 V45.83 (28.12.2007): - fixed bug in asyncio dispatcher, which
                        could have lead to a stale file lock,
                        thus memory loss, in case of DOS fallback
                        during AsyncIO availability

 V45.78 (2.10.2007):  - applied fix to new IO dispatcher
                        (maintenance, only)

                      - Prefs: - added "Reset" option for
                                 default settings

 V45.75 (17.9.2007):  - previous re-entrancy change reverted

 V45.74 (2.9.2007):   - enhanced async/normal IO dispatcher
                      - now fully re-entrant
                      - MOS: version still was at v45.71
                      - minor changes

 V45.73 (5.8.2007):   - fixed bogus memory allocation (non-pooled)
                        (-> Thomas Klein)

 V45.72 (5.8.2007):   - added missing icons for prefs items
                        (-> Thomas Klein)

 V45.71 (4.8.2007):   - significant speedup in displaying tiled
                        "true color" images using some caching
                      - more memory-related optimizations

 V45.70 (1.8.2007):   - 68k: removed all V40 legacy code
                      - 68k: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                      - 68k: previously, V43-code was not used prior V44

                      - MOS: reverted to faster compiler settings

                      - memory-related optimizations
                      - added prefs program
                      - added "custom modes" support
                      - added configuration options for tiled loading,
                        tile section and anim loading

 V45.66 (23.7.2007):  - 68k: also uses new screenmode functions now
                      - 68k: 030/040/060 versions linked (wrong)
                             math library (with no effect)
                      - now uses asyncio.library if available
                      - now dynamically adjusts read-ahead buffers
                        depending on available system memory

 V45.65 (22.7.2007):  - address change

                      - fully reworked GIF parser
                      - improved error handling,
                        robustness and stability
                      - now supports tiled images (**)
                      - now supports "truecolor" GIFs,
                        i.e. tiled images with
                        different (upto) 256 color
                        palettes now are loaded as
                        single 24 bit image (**)
                      - GIF animations are treated
                        exactly the same way (unless
                        tiles are turned off, you
                        always get the last animation
                        screen as resulting image) (**)
                      - now supports image disposal
                        flags (where it makes sense,
                        i.e. in the context of tiled
                        images)
                      - fixed at least one more depth-
                        related bug (uncritical)
                      - various optimizations
                      - consumes more memory now;
                        reason is that optimizing the
                        new decoding routines for memory
                        usage would in turn make it harder
                        to support V40 in parallel to V43;
                        under MOS however memory usage
                        is not such a problem

                      - MOS: now uses global pooling
                      - 68k: now uses V43 methods if available

                        (**) currently tile support cannot
                             be switched off and anim handling
                             is not yet configurable; this may change

                        (***) yet no RGBA support for 24 bit
                              tiled images (losing transparency)

 V45.62 (25.5.2007):  - memory allocation routine now adapts itself
                        better to system config (pool adjustment)
                      - optimized pool configuration in general

 V45.57 (13.1.2007):  - MOS dt version ID still was 45.49 (updated)
                      - removed old workaround, which always
                        increased a depth of 1 to a depth of 2
                      - do not set interleaved flag when allocating
                        bitmaps of depth 1
                      - tested under MOS resp. WinUAE

 V45.55 (26.11.2006): - updated installer
                      - minor fixes in .guide

 V45.49 (24.3.2006):  - speed-optimized 68k version

 V45.46 (18.2.2006):  - prepared for OM_GET and DTA_Methods

 V45.31 (29.1.2006):  - fixed spatch problem, finally

 V45.30 (16.1.2006):  - various minor fixes
                      - now DONATION WARE (see www.ar-kleinert.de)

 V45.27 (24.5.2005):  - Installer fix (spatch was missing in c)
                        (Luke, Timo Hegemann)
                      - fixed AmigaGuide (space too much...)
                        (Timo Hegemann)
                      - 68k version now also uses memory pools

 V45.26 (14.5.2005):  - Installer fix

 V45.25 (13.5.2005):  - integrated MorphOS version
                      - small improvements

 V45.1  (08.07.2004): - first release

@ENDNODE
